---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Kubernetes Networking & Services" 
  description="Interactive visualization of Kubernetes networking — pod networking, CNI, Services, kube-proxy, DNS, Ingress, and Network Policies"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" }, 
    { label: "Kubernetes", href: "/kubernetes/" },
    { label: "Networking", href: "/kubernetes/networking/" }
  ]}
>
  <div class="viz-container">
    <header class="viz-header">
      <h1>☸️ Kubernetes Networking &amp; Services</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Pod IPs, Services, DNS, Ingress &amp; Network Policies — How Traffic Flows</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section class="overview-section">
      <div class="overview-card">
        <p>
          In Kubernetes, every <strong>Pod gets its own IP address</strong>. Pods communicate across nodes
          on a <em>flat network</em> — no NAT between pods. The <strong>Container Network Interface (CNI)</strong>
          plugin allocates IPs and sets up routing. <strong>Services</strong> provide stable virtual IPs
          and load-balance traffic to Pod backends. <strong>kube-proxy</strong> programs the data plane
          (iptables, IPVS, or eBPF) to forward traffic. <strong>CoreDNS</strong> enables service discovery
          via DNS names like <code>my-svc.default.svc.cluster.local</code>. For external access,
          <strong>Ingress</strong> provides L7 routing, and <strong>Network Policies</strong> act as
          firewall rules for pod-to-pod traffic.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Pod Networking Model -->
    <section class="explain-section">
      <h2>🔌 Pod Networking Model</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">The fundamental rules every Kubernetes network must satisfy.</p>
      <div class="explain-grid">
        <div class="explain-card highlight-card">
          <h3>📦 Every Pod Gets an IP</h3>
          <p>
            Each Pod receives a <strong>unique, routable IP</strong> from the cluster CIDR. Containers
            within a Pod share the same network namespace — they communicate via <code>localhost</code>.
            Pod-to-Pod traffic uses real IPs, no port mapping needed.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="explain-card">
          <h3>🌐 Flat Network</h3>
          <p>
            All Pods can reach all other Pods <strong>without NAT</strong>, regardless of which node
            they're on. This is enforced by the CNI plugin, which sets up overlay networks (VXLAN),
            direct routing (BGP), or cloud-native VPC routing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="explain-card">
          <h3>🔧 CNI Plugins</h3>
          <p>
            The <strong>Container Network Interface</strong> is the standard API. Popular CNI plugins:
            <strong>Calico</strong> (BGP routing + policy), <strong>Cilium</strong> (eBPF-based),
            <strong>Flannel</strong> (simple overlay), <strong>Weave</strong> (mesh overlay).
            The kubelet calls the CNI plugin when a Pod starts to assign its IP and configure routes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Service Types -->
    <section class="explain-section">
      <h2>🎯 Service Types</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Services provide stable endpoints and load balancing for ephemeral Pods.</p>
      <div class="service-types-row">
        <div class="service-type-card" id="svcClusterIP">
          <div class="svc-icon">🏠</div>
          <h3>ClusterIP</h3>
          <p>Internal-only virtual IP. Default type. Only reachable from within the cluster. kube-proxy programs rules to DNAT traffic from the VIP to backend Pod IPs.</p>
          <div class="svc-example">
            <code>10.96.0.10:80 → Pod1:8080, Pod2:8080</code>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-type-card" id="svcNodePort">
          <div class="svc-icon">🚪</div>
          <h3>NodePort</h3>
          <p>Exposes the service on a static port (30000–32767) on every node's IP. External clients hit <code>NodeIP:NodePort</code>. Builds on ClusterIP.</p>
          <div class="svc-example">
            <code>&lt;NodeIP&gt;:31234 → ClusterIP:80 → Pods</code>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="service-type-card" id="svcLoadBalancer">
          <div class="svc-icon">☁️</div>
          <h3>LoadBalancer</h3>
          <p>Provisions a cloud load balancer (AWS ELB, GCP LB) that routes external traffic to NodePort. Gets a public IP. Builds on NodePort + ClusterIP.</p>
          <div class="svc-example">
            <code>ELB:80 → NodePort → ClusterIP → Pods</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Interactive Cluster Visualization -->
    <section class="cluster-section">
      <h2>🖧 Interactive Network Cluster</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Send a request and watch it route through Service → kube-proxy → Pod. Compare proxy modes.</p>

      <div class="sim-layout">
        <!-- Config Panel -->
        <div class="config-panel">
          <h3>Request Configuration</h3>

          <div class="config-group">
            <label>Target Service</label>
            <select id="targetSvc" class="config-select">
              <option value="web-svc">web-svc (ClusterIP)</option>
              <option value="api-svc">api-svc (NodePort)</option>
              <option value="db-svc">db-svc (ClusterIP)</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div class="config-group">
            <label>kube-proxy Mode</label>
            <select id="proxyMode" class="config-select">
              <option value="iptables">iptables (default)</option>
              <option value="ipvs">IPVS (hash-based)</option>
              <option value="ebpf">eBPF (Cilium)</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div class="config-group">
            <label>Source</label>
            <select id="requestSource" class="config-select">
              <option value="pod">Pod (in-cluster)</option>
              <option value="external">External client</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <button id="sendReqBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">▶ Send Request</button>
          <button id="resetClusterBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
        </div>

        <!-- Cluster View -->
        <div class="cluster-view">
          <div class="net-cluster" id="netCluster">
            <!-- Rendered by JS -->
          </div>

          <!-- Trace Log -->
          <div class="sched-log-wrapper">
            <h4>📋 Network Trace</h4>
            <div class="sched-log" id="traceLog">
              <div class="log-empty">Configure a request and click "Send Request"...</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- kube-proxy Modes Comparison -->
    <section class="explain-section">
      <h2>⚙️ kube-proxy Modes</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Three ways to implement Service routing in the data plane.</p>
      <div class="explain-grid">
        <div class="explain-card">
          <h3>📋 iptables (Default)</h3>
          <p>
            Creates <strong>DNAT rules</strong> in iptables for each Service/endpoint pair.
            Uses <code>random</code> probability for load balancing. Linear rule traversal:
            <strong>O(n)</strong> with number of services. Fine for small clusters (&lt;1000 services).
          </p>
          <div class="mode-stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Latency</span>
            <div class="stat-bar"><div class="stat-fill" style="width:60%"></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mode-stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Scalability</span>
            <div class="stat-bar"><div class="stat-fill low" style="width:35%"></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="explain-card highlight-card">
          <h3>⚡ IPVS (Hash-Based)</h3>
          <p>
            Uses the Linux <strong>IP Virtual Server</strong> in the kernel. Hash-based lookup:
            <strong>O(1)</strong> regardless of service count. Supports multiple algorithms:
            round-robin, least-connections, source hashing. Better at scale (&gt;1000 services).
          </p>
          <div class="mode-stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Latency</span>
            <div class="stat-bar"><div class="stat-fill" style="width:40%"></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mode-stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Scalability</span>
            <div class="stat-bar"><div class="stat-fill high" style="width:85%"></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="explain-card">
          <h3>🐝 eBPF (Cilium)</h3>
          <p>
            Replaces kube-proxy entirely. Attaches <strong>BPF programs</strong> to socket and TC hooks.
            Bypasses iptables/netfilter completely. <strong>O(1)</strong> lookups via BPF maps.
            Lowest latency, best scalability, but requires a modern kernel (5.4+) and Cilium CNI.
          </p>
          <div class="mode-stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Latency</span>
            <div class="stat-bar"><div class="stat-fill high" style="width:20%"></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mode-stat">
            <span class="stat-label">Scalability</span>
            <div class="stat-bar"><div class="stat-fill high" style="width:95%"></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DNS Section -->
    <section class="dns-section">
      <h2>🔎 DNS &amp; Service Discovery</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">CoreDNS resolves service names to ClusterIPs. Watch a DNS query resolve.</p>

      <div class="dns-demo">
        <div class="dns-input-row">
          <label>Query:</label>
          <input type="text" id="dnsQuery" class="dns-input" value="web-svc.default.svc.cluster.local" readonly>
          <button id="dnsResolveBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🔎 Resolve</button>
        </div>
        <div class="dns-presets">
          <button class="dns-preset" data-query="web-svc.default.svc.cluster.local">web-svc.default</button>
          <button class="dns-preset" data-query="api-svc.kube-system.svc.cluster.local">api-svc.kube-system</button>
          <button class="dns-preset" data-query="db-svc.default.svc.cluster.local">db-svc.default</button>
          <button class="dns-preset" data-query="web-svc.default">short name</button>
        </div>
        <div class="dns-viz" id="dnsViz">
          <div class="dns-step-row" id="dnsSteps">
            <!-- Rendered by JS -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Ingress -->
    <section class="explain-section">
      <h2>🚀 Ingress</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">L7 HTTP routing — host-based, path-based, with TLS termination.</p>

      <div class="ingress-demo">
        <div class="ingress-rules" id="ingressRules">
          <div class="ingress-rule">
            <div class="ingress-host">app.example.com</div>
            <div class="ingress-paths">
              <div class="ingress-path" data-target="web-svc">
                <span class="path-match">/</span>
                <span class="path-arrow">→</span>
                <span class="path-backend">web-svc:80</span>
              </div>
              <div class="ingress-path" data-target="api-svc">
                <span class="path-match">/api/*</span>
                <span class="path-arrow">→</span>
                <span class="path-backend">api-svc:8080</span>
              </div>
              <div class="ingress-path" data-target="ws-svc">
                <span class="path-match">/ws</span>
                <span class="path-arrow">→</span>
                <span class="path-backend">ws-svc:9090</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ingress-rule">
            <div class="ingress-host">admin.example.com</div>
            <div class="ingress-paths">
              <div class="ingress-path" data-target="admin-svc">
                <span class="path-match">/</span>
                <span class="path-arrow">→</span>
                <span class="path-backend">admin-svc:3000</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ingress-test">
          <label>Test URL:</label>
          <input type="text" id="ingressUrl" class="dns-input" value="https://app.example.com/api/users">
          <button id="ingressTestBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🚀 Route</button>
          <div class="ingress-result" id="ingressResult"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Network Policies -->
    <section class="netpol-section">
      <h2>🛡️ Network Policies</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Firewall rules for Pods. Control ingress and egress traffic with label selectors.</p>

      <div class="netpol-demo">
        <div class="netpol-editor">
          <h3>Policy Editor</h3>
          <div class="config-group">
            <label>Target Pods</label>
            <select id="polTarget" class="config-select">
              <option value="web">app=web</option>
              <option value="api">app=api</option>
              <option value="db">app=db</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="config-group">
            <label>Ingress: Allow From</label>
            <div class="checkbox-group">
              <label class="cb-label"><input type="checkbox" id="polAllowWeb" checked> app=web</label>
              <label class="cb-label"><input type="checkbox" id="polAllowApi" checked> app=api</label>
              <label class="cb-label"><input type="checkbox" id="polAllowDb"> app=db</label>
              <label class="cb-label"><input type="checkbox" id="polAllowExt"> external</label>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="config-group">
            <label>Egress: Allow To</label>
            <div class="checkbox-group">
              <label class="cb-label"><input type="checkbox" id="polEgressDns" checked> DNS (port 53)</label>
              <label class="cb-label"><input type="checkbox" id="polEgressDb" checked> app=db</label>
              <label class="cb-label"><input type="checkbox" id="polEgressExt"> internet</label>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button id="polApplyBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🛡️ Apply Policy</button>
          <button id="polResetBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
        </div>

        <div class="netpol-viz">
          <div class="netpol-cluster" id="netpolCluster">
            <!-- Rendered by JS -->
          </div>
          <div class="netpol-yaml" id="netpolYaml">
            <h4>Generated YAML</h4>
            <pre id="netpolYamlCode"></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="viz-footer">
      <p>Based on the <a href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/" target="_blank">Kubernetes Networking Documentation</a></p>
    </footer>

    <div class="share-buttons">
      <span>Share this visualization:</span>
      <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Interactive%20Kubernetes%20Networking%20visualizer&url=https://systeminternals.dev/kubernetes/networking/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">𝕏 Twitter</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://systeminternals.dev/kubernetes/networking/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">in LinkedIn</a>
      <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/submitlink?u=https://systeminternals.dev/kubernetes/networking/&t=Interactive%20Kubernetes%20Networking%20Visualizer" target="_blank" class="share-btn">🟧 Hacker News</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .viz-container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .viz-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .viz-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, #60a5fa, #34d399, #a78bfa);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .section-desc {
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* Overview */
  .overview-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .overview-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.1), rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.05));
    border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #ccc;
  }

  .overview-card strong { color: #fff; }
  .overview-card em { color: #34d399; font-style: normal; font-weight: 500; }
  .overview-card code {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #22c55e;
  }
  .overview-card a { color: #60a5fa; }

  /* Action Buttons */
  .action-btn {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .action-btn:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  .primary-btn {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #60a5fa, #3b82f6);
    color: white;
  }

  .primary-btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4);
  }

  .reset-btn {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    color: #aaa;
  }

  .reset-btn:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2); color: #fff; }

  /* Explain sections */
  .explain-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .explain-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .explain-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
  }

  .explain-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .explain-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #aaa;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .explain-card strong { color: #fff; }
  .explain-card em { color: #60a5fa; font-style: normal; }
  .explain-card code {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #22c55e;
  }

  .highlight-card {
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.08), rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.04));
  }

  /* Service Types */
  .service-types-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .service-type-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.3s;
    cursor: default;
  }

  .service-type-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.4);
    background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.05);
  }

  .service-type-card.active-svc {
    border-color: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.6);
    background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.08);
    box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.15);
  }

  .svc-icon { font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }

  .service-type-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .service-type-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #aaa;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .service-type-card code {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #22c55e;
  }

  .svc-example {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 8px 12px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #60a5fa;
  }

  /* Sim Layout */
  .cluster-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .sim-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .config-panel {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  .config-panel h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .config-group {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .config-group label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #aaa;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .config-group label strong {
    color: #60a5fa;
  }

  .config-select {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 8px 10px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #ddd;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .config-panel .action-btn {
    width: 100%;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  /* Network Cluster Visualization */
  .cluster-view {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .net-cluster {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .net-node {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 14px;
    transition: all 0.4s;
    position: relative;
  }

  .net-node.active-node {
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.6);
    background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.05);
  }

  .net-node-name {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .net-node-ip {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: #888;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .net-pods {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .net-pod {
    padding: 6px 10px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: all 0.4s;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
  }

  .net-pod.web { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2); color: #93c5fd; border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3); }
  .net-pod.api { background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.2); color: #c4b5fd; border-color: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.3); }
  .net-pod.db { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.2); color: #fbbf24; border-color: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.3); }

  .net-pod.targeted {
    box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.4);
    border-color: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.7);
    animation: podPulse 0.6s ease;
  }

  .net-svc-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 6px;
    background: rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.2);
    color: #34d399;
    border: 1px solid rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.3);
  }

  .net-proxy-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    color: #f472b6;
